verbose_text: In conclusion, the present study suggested that the lack of endogenous PTH may decrease expression of VEGF in BMSCs or osteoblasts via downregulation of the PKA/pAKT/HIF1alpha/VEGF pathway, which causes reduced angiogenesis and thereby affects endochondral bone formation, ultimately leading to delayed fracture healing.
evidence: PKA/pAKT/HIF1alpha/VEGF pathway, which causes reduced angiogenesis
